They do list three occasionally-Country Party MHRs from Tasmania back in the 1920s. (BTW, 'NAT' there == Nationalist Party, not 'National Party', which in the early 1920s was an entity split from the Labor Party in South Australia.)

This 'National' Party has never had a member from South Australia either, though it is still registered there.
